The paper discusses the generation of adversarial examples for deep networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science. Given that the paper focuses on the optimization algorithms used to generate these examples, it is most likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of defences against adversarial attacks, which falls under the sub-field of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of genetic and direct-search algorithms, which are common in the sub-field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Therefore, the most likely categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.NE, in that order.
